can you imagine us as soldiers coming home from a war? we are veterans of a battlefield where the masculine severely terrorized and harmed the feminine. the ongoing war fractured our sense of reality and safety. so can you invite us warriors/veterans into your hometown and ask us to speak about our war history so it can come into the light and be healed for us all? let’s honor our soldiers of war. this is the perspective i am asking you to take. can you? can you please for the sake of humanity treat us with kindness and trust that our healing process might be loud, it might be scary, it might be really uncomfoable to witness. and if you can’t witness then it’s okay to leave the room but don’t dictate or try to gauge my process. i am rebihing equality. it did exist at one time, i’m asking us all to try and remember.

text:
yesterday i let my anger and discuss release out of my body onto the dancefloor. 
this last week american's headline triggered my personal wounding with sexual abuse and abuse of power in a big way. i actually started to physically feel sick as the week went by, which set off my inner alarm system... so i talked about it with my beloved yesterday and felt held and seen with so much love by him. 
today i feel so clear, energized and grounded after having my physical catharsis. 
feeling my anger on the dance floor allowed me to reconnect with my life force energy and to access my voice, my creative personal power.

text:
"the most painful state of being is remembering the future, particularly the one you'll never have." - kierkegaard.

threats.

working on the sprinkler system yesterday, i paused for a moment to roll the trash out to the curb.

as i moved the trash cans, i revealed a threat... a western #diamondback rattlesnake.

i had no idea he was there. nor did he announce his presence. so, i went on about my business and probably walked past him 10 times before i ever saw him.

he was just coiled up there. looked like he had been feeding on some of the numerous field mice and was #fat and lethargic.

i hate to #kill anything without cause, but leaving him in the yard or chasing him into a neighbor's yard could threaten lives.

ultimately, i went for his head with a rake. and, he quickly dodged my strike. i immediately started to second guess my #strategy... he wasn't as lethargic as he first appeared.

i went for him again. after a sketchy #combat, i pinned him successfully for decapitation. bagged him so the head could pose no threat, and disposed the carcass.

prior to noticing him, i had no knowledge i was ever in #danger. i didn't know what i didn't know. and, i placed my future in jeopardy being ignorant.

much like each of us do when dealing with the dynamics of moving others toward our #vision or an outcome that could better our organizations, relationships, or health.

in reading principles, by ray dalio i see the #ignorance i have brought to many situations in the past, ways i can move forward positively, and the futility of an organization filled with people who are unable to process harsh criticism as anything but a personal attack.

no growth comes from that place. yet, we go through #life unaware of the threats these behaviors pose to our future.

the threats they pose to our #dreams and aspirations... all very real, but just as subtle and unseen as that rattlesnake.

the biggest #threat of all? it's not knowing the ways we sabotage ourselves and ultimately those around us.

do you really know yourself? share your thoughts below.

site + light.
j

text:
my forever mood! i can think of so many ways that god has blessed me and that is what holds me together when the challenges of life come upon me! tell me, how has god blessed you? come vibe with me. 👇🏾 i'll share first: 
he delivered me from abusive relationships.

he healed my broken heart.

he is a good, good father to me and my children.

he kept me alive when suicide wanted to claim my life.

when you shift your perspective from what has not gone your way to one of gratitude, appreciation, and humility it will make a world of difference. believe you are blessed, because you are!

text: (tw for references to sexual violence) @wildsoulhealing recently shared an invitation to send a strength card in the mail to christine blasey ford, a sign of appreciation for the testimony she shared with the senate and the world last week. this was such a touching idea; the way she carried herself in that hearing was a perfect embodiment of strength, of using gentle but direct action in the face of intimidation. 🦁 i started thinking about all the cards i wish i could send. how the woman raped by brock turner exemplifies the two of swords, strong in her boundaries, insistent that she be heard without sacrificing her anonymity. ⚔️ i thought of carla brooks, an elderly woman raped in her own home by someone i called friend; carla has used her privilege as a respected member of her community to draw attention to the backlog of rape kits and to proclaim that victims have no cause for shame. i'd like to drop a tarot card in her mailbox, maybe the page of swords in honor of her bold voice and pursuit of justice. 📖 the untold millions who've been abused, assaulted, disregarded -- i just want to wrap them up in the love of the empress, in the deep knowing that they deserved to receive better than what they got. 👑 so many more. too many for a caption. dozens of decks' worth of cards, sent to every corner of the planet. emblems of our shared suffering, our shared humanity, our shared strength. #metoo #ibelieveher #thankyoudrford #thankyouanitahill #smithwaitecentennial #strength  #tarot #utahtarot #ogdentarot #daviscountytarot  #laytontarot #slctarot #saltlakecity #laytonutah #mormontarot #tarotcommunity #tarotreadersofinstagram #taroteverydamnday

text: for me in the 20 yrs i’ve been practicing yoga, my hips didn’t start to become more flexible until i started doing the hard work of addressing the energy of emotion and trauma. sitting in it, sitting with it, closing my eyes to see it, feel it more multidimensional to know it well. which can help it become a source of strength and power to move forward in your life all while bringing peace to your mind and flexibility to the body. yoga and meditation teach us to deepen into ourselves and be present. come to your mat, a class, my class, a cushion, a chair, the floor...it doesn’t much matter. just close your eyes, breathe deeply and dive into your body’s wisdom. as one of my more recent teachers so simply stated “we are all just energy moving through form...and we all have unanswerable whys” ~ @manorama9 i pulled a card from the archangel michael deck which reinforced “guarded and protected”...#metoomovement #metoo #yoga #yogateacher #shareyourexperience #youarenotalone #strengthinnumbers #couragetoheal #mindbodyspirit #mindbodyconnection #survivorchildhoodsexualabuse #speakup #thetimeisnow #ourpainisourstrength #agnistambhasana #doublepigeon #firelogpose #oraclecards #archangelmichael

text:
my most basic principle for life.

its so damn simple. if you don't know what someone's going through, don't add your uneducated 2 cents. if you don't understand someone's reasons for doing something - ask them and try to understand.

i'm going to be touching more on mental health because in this social media crazy world that we live in, it can become such a dangerous playground. but it can also be a tool to reach out to people who cannot see the point of their existence anymore. i have been at that point and i have also lost friends who got past that point. its an all too common feeling and im sure most of you can sadly relate.

so it's simple. be kind. dont judge. preach love.

and happy tuesday.

text: this morning i had this conversation with a woman i had just met: “this kavanaugh business is a mess. that woman, i’m wondering, why didn’t she say anything before, when it happened?” i asked, “have you ever been assaulted?” “yes, i have.” she said. “and, did you tell anyone?” “no i didn’t. but wait, here’s why. i was young, a teenager. and my mother knew this hair dresser and she asked him to give me a job. he said, sure, have her come work for me. but he had other plans. and after it happened i told him he had to stop. and so he fired me. i went home and my mother said, what happened? i said, he fired me, i did the shampoo wrong. but see, i knew that if i told her what happened, someone was going to prison. i thought about what my father would have done when he found out, and i didn’t want our lives to be destroyed over this. so i never told them.” i took my sunglasses off and looked the woman in the eye. “i’m really sorry that happened to you.” “thank you, “ she said. “it was a long time ago, almost fifty years ago.” it occurred to me, this may be the first time she’s told anyone about this, ever. “you did what you needed to do to take care of yourself and the people you love,” i said. “you considered the situation, considered your options, and you made the choice that was going to keep yourself and your family safe.” she told me, “i see the way they look at that ford woman, everyone looking at her like she’s nothing. and they don’t believe her. and they blame her.” “it’s awful,” i said. “i asked myself, was it what i wore? was i flirting? but no, i was just being nice - he was my employer!” i looked her in the eye and said, “it’s not your fault.” she held my gaze and said, “thank you.” “it was 100% not your fault. you didn’t do anything wrong. this was not your fault.” she said, “if i knew other women who had been assaulted by him, i would say something. women need to stick together. i contribute to planned parenthood. we need to be able to take care of ourselves. and the culture needs to change.” “yup, it sure does.” survivors need better options. we need leaders who support survivors and are committed to ending rape culture.

text:
i need your face!! if you’re sick of the patriarchy and all the fucking bullshit that happens to women, men, and everyone in between, and want to be part of my project, lend me your face. guys, gals, and non-binary pals are all welcome. i plan on making stickers and possibly prints of these and what you see here is just a rough sketch. 
my goal is diversity here and i want everyone who sees this project to be able to find themselves represented in it. 
what you can do to help: send me a selfie in the same pose with a pissed off face (or sad, or any other emotion the subject sparks) and i’ll do the rest. optional: a short phrase (5 words or less) about how you feel about sexism, racism, classism, homophobia, and transphobia—whatever affects and pisses you off most. 
i haven’t decided on a style yet but i plan on adding these phrases/quotes to the piece so i would greatly appreciate each portrait having their own personal words. you can comment here, dm me, or hit me up on twitter @ dani_destructo. thank you!! #feminism #intersectionalfeminism #fedup #womensrights #sexism #racism #transphobia #homophobia #nomore #metoo #enoughisenough

text:
{part 2 of 3}
growing up, leah wanted to be a famous actress and full time mom.  in a broken home, she saw acting as a form to bring everyone together to laugh and make memories.  eventually, she chose not to pursue acting after all, and then felt like she didn’t have any direction. to add to the hardship, she lived in a single mom home, and they moved often. leah was used to being the new girl at school, moving 9 times in 13 years. despite the trials that came with that, leah eventually graduated high school with honors. inspired and aided by her sister who joined the navy, leah chose to pursue a career in the army. there, she would meet her husband and they would marry and have a child. unfortunately, they were kept apart. since that wasn’t a life she wanted for her child, both leah and her husband left the military and began their lives as a stay-at-home mom and fireman.
♥️
during her time in the military, leah struggled in silence, but now she feels like it’s time for her story to be told. she feels it would be therapeutic for her, and it will be a beacon of light for the silent suffering that goes on in the military. although she is thanked often for her service, she is infiltrated with a sense of shame because too often, she feels that every day americans  have no idea about the ugliness that exists. during her service, she was ostracized for standing up for what was right. she was often overlooked for positions because she wouldn’t commit sexual acts for advancement. peers were promoted because they would. her integrity was questioned on many occasions, and that is a hot button for her. for what she endured, leah developed an anxiety disorder with chronic depression. thankfully, her loving husband and god have gotten her through it. she has a message and a direction now, and wants to motivate others through her work.
#jhportraitartist #thebeautywithinproject #followyourdreams #metoo
hmu @marleneg_beauty thank you!

text:
my husband is a |g o o d| man.
-
in a time like this in our nation, let’s not forget that all men are not evil. the action of one, or a few, does not define them all. -
they do not all belong to the #boysclub -
my husband and i talk about sex bc if the other isn’t in the mood, how would we know otherwise? we are not #entitled to one another’s bodies and most certainly aren’t on this earth just to #pleasure one another.
-
before he ever kissed me for the first time, he asked for #permission . he still asks for kisses if he wants them, and so do i.
-
it’s called #consent and even #married couples ask for it.
-
he lifts me up. he supports my path and respects my truth. good men are out there.
-
#ibelieveher -
i believe dr. ford is speaking her truth and that it’s not our job to judge her or analyze anything she says.
-
i believe that #boyswillbeboys is incredibly outdated. #boys and #men will be held accountable for their fucking actions, women too.
-
i believe people change and deserve to not have their lives dismantled. at the same time, own up to your shit. -
i too didn’t tell anyone when i was harassed for years and i should have. -
you have no right to look up my skirt when i walk up the stairs, or to ask me to do it again. it is not ok to comment on my ass when i wear pants to work either. my shoes don’t say ‘come fuck me’ and no i don’t want to hear that shit. it makes you look creepy, they’re shoes dude.
-
women deserve to be respected. in this world we have a lot of power and it’s well overdue that we lift women up. -
women, empower yourselves. share your story. heal. the world needs your gifts. -
i don’t know about you, but i’m here to shake shit up.
-
we are the storm.
-

text: i was around 6 or 7 when my sexual abuse began. i don’t really want to get into the details on social media, but i think it’s worth mentioning that i didn’t speak a word about it until freshman year of college. i had a psychology teacher that encouraged us to write about the things we’ve buried too deep to talk about. i found friends in college that helped me cope, went to a counselor that helped me see jesus in all of it. now i’m married to a man that loves me and accepts me in ways i never thought i deserved because of the pain and confusion i encountered when i was a kid. sexual abuse should never be a partisan issue, it should be a humanity issue. i don’t care who you are and whether you agree or not... i believe her. and i stand with those of you who are too scared to speak up, for fear of experiencing the same reactions christine blasey ford got. #metoo

text:
survivor medicine🌿 below is a list of plants that can be helpful for survivors. cw for nondetailed mention of what we've survived + how it can effect us
.
.
fellow survivors, we know these days are hard. here on turtle island we live in a rape culture garbage fire colonial society that was built on this kind of violence + continues to uphold it everyday. sexualized violence disproportionately effects bipoc folks esp women + femmes, nonbinary folks, queer, trans + 2spirit folks. rapists getting away with shit + gaining power is nothing new, but fresh wounds still hurt.
.
.
as a survivor of many kinds of sexualized violence since early childhood, i can say that working with plant medicines has been deeply transformative in my healing + is a main reason why i'm still here. below are some plant friends i regularly call on to assist me + that i've seen be very supportive for clients/friends over the past 15+ yrs i've been offering medicines + care to survivors. .
.
all of these herbs can be taken as tea, general dose (unless otherwise noted) is 4 tablespoons of herb per quart of boiled water, cover + let steep for 15min. drink as needed:
.
🌿hawthorn offers protection + support while grieving + assists in releasing that which no longer serves us. esp helpful for heart palpitations that come with stress.
.
🌿wood betony (stachys) helps move from a place of panic to a place of processing the feels. helps us come back into our bodies when disassociating (when that is a safe choice).
.
🌿milky oat deeply soothes stress + repairs a burnt out nervous system. esp helpful when beyond capacity + feeling like yr gonna break.
.
🌿chamomile is soothing + esp helpful when stress/trauma causes digestive upset or interrupts digestive process.
.
🌿rose tends to emotional wounds, comforts in times of deep sadness, helps to tighten boundaries of our hearts. use 2tbs instead of 4 as it's very drying.
.
🌿lemonbalm is calming + uplifting to depressive feels. as an antiviral it's helpful for stress induced viral outbreaks.
.
🌿mugwort unblocks + clears stagnant energy, is fiercely protective + can assist in working stuff out in our dreams.
.
.
✨may you always be protected✨

text:
#whyididntreport 
the first person i told straight after, said to me: you must have been drunk. 
the second person i told said: he must have been drunk. 
the third person i told said: you must be mistaken 💔 #thatswhy 😒

when i did feel the need to report? 8 years later, i worked with mentally handicapped people and one day at work he stood behind me, called me by my name, tried to hug me... i panicked, not for me, but for the women under his care 😥 i told my manager, but not much could be done because he didnt have a record, he was allowed to work there. 
those were the roughest months i ever had at work. 3 months in i get called in by hr, if i wanted to tell my story again... and they asked me to officialy report it to the police. turns out he assaulted a co-worker. 
i went to the police and they asked me why i didnt report this sooner, because they had a big file on him already, but no current case to pin it on him, i apologised 🙄 
i was asked to testify at a hearing so my employer could fire him, i did and got dragged through the mud in front of my managers and hr by him and his attorney.they were able to fire him, but they were not allowed to disclose why if asked for references. i was broken again... a year later, i get a call from the police officer who took my statement. the guy was arrested, not because of his long time record for sexual assault, but for fraud. at least he did get punished for something, the officer said to me.... 🙄🤔 why didnt i report? why didnt the women before me report? 
because "you must have been drunk" 
because "he's such a good man"
because "he's very involved in the community"
because " you must have been mistaken"

he grabbed a 17yr old, tried to undress her, tried to kiss her, tried to force himself on to her... he was 45yrs old, father of 2 of my friends,  coach of the girls soccer team, pillar of the community

#metoo #understandme #fear #confused #ibelieveher #mystory #didmytimeintherapy

text:
💃🏼 what the world tells me to look like 💃🏼
- hot topic.. i am a personal trainer and i train lots of women, who come to me and say they want to look something like this.. - firstly there is nothing wrong with her body and the way she looks, but most of this is genetics..
- you will never look like anyone else! - i think the media makes us think if we don’t like look like we aren’t desirable. i don’t look anything like her but i’m 100% okay with that.
- for years when i was over weight i dreamed of a body i would never have, as the years went on and i started to train i realised i never wanted anyone else’s body but my own. - to work on what i have and what i am and be the best version of me! - i’m sure this model has insecurities as we all do
- i think we should just aspire to being the best version of ourselves, physically and mentally and stop comparing! - im just very aware that being a pt can be a lot about image and i really want to break that and make exercise something to always be enjoyed not an effort because we have to look a certain way! - anyways rant over, this is me loving my body and everything i am inside and out☺️
-  xxxxxxx . #metoo #bodyconfidence #fitnessgoals #victoriasecretmodel #beingmyownmodel #goals #mentalhealth #workout #happiness #beinghappyismygoal #trainning #nutrition #personaltrainer #stopcomparing #mybody #myskin

text:
here’s me being a #parkour gypsy ninja... because today i published a blog series about #internetprivacy on #socialmedia. 
i think this applies to all #onlinecoaches #dietitiansofinstagram #rd2be’s #nutritionists #personaltrainers #fitness peeps & others who have a public account to promote themselves & their business online! let’s talk about how we keep our accounts secure and how we post to keep our bodies safe in real life. 
why did i write this? it has a lot to do with my own stalker experience and how it's changed what goes through my head when i post on social media: why i don't tag my real location, why i don't post a lot of pics of my friends/family on instagram, how i operate my business address & phone number. check the link in my bio for my online safety tips for social media.

it's not just about being a woman online, this could certainly apply to men as well! but i do think it's significantly scarier to think about what someone could do with information about my location as a woman. men don't worry about rape so much, do they? 
when i sat in court for my harassment prevention order, i saw countless women filing for a restraining order, and men were always the defendants. unfortunately, i think this means that women also have to be more careful online, just as we are more careful in real life walking to our cars or walking home at night. #metoo
📸: @lyssadeeee

text:
in light of the ford vs kavanaugh case, i have decided to share my story, almost 10 years later.

i am speaking out now because i am sick of hearing, "why didn't she say anything sooner?" so here i am, putting myself out there, showing ford my support, in order to try and help others understand why we don't speak up.

i didn't speak up during the #metoo movement because i didn't feel my story counted as i did consent. however, that consent was pressured and i don't believe i was even fit to consent as i wasn't fully informed due to my abstinence only education. plus the age difference between him and me also probably nullifies the consent as well, despite the fact i was 18.

you can read my full story on the blog: https://goo.gl/4kmzia

link is also temporarily in my bio.

text:
back to the source.
that's the natural instinct of any alive being to protect oneself by going back to what you know, where you feel/felt protected.
i'm now going through a very complicated divorce where my ex-partner is not accepting the situation and decided to revenge by sending abusive content ,lies and defamation about me to all my friends through instagram. 
my friends, it made me understand what is true #friendship, a chaotic situation such as being a #metoo victim, plus a divorced women on a top of being a #cancersurvivor actually became a real blessing, i believe that i created that situation because i asked god to move away from me anything/anyone that does not serve my higher self, that does not make me feel joyful, that does not make me smile. so god replied, and so many things have been moving, in a way i wouldn't imagine. some friends moved away, by fear, but so many people i didn't know as friends appeared to be really great friends, who are supporting me more than i could imagine.

all this is happening these past weeks when i suddenly decided to go back to the source, to my family in europe, to my childhood in yugoslavia and i realised what was the unconditional love that we talk about so much in bali and others spiritual places... unconditional love is the way my parents love me, with my craziness, even when i'm eating an apple, barefoot in the garden with 10 degrees outside while sungazing without sunglasses! or when i'm saging the house before to sleep or when i dry fast for 2 days...they don't understand me, nor they need because their love for me is un-conditional. whatever i do, say, however insane or silly it looks it doesn't matter how old i'm getting, they still love me the same. they are my creators, my source.

to be continued...

.

text:
thinking of all my middle and high school girls who seem to so easily forget who they are, (including the high school version of myself in this)  today i was so compelled to remind a young girl that beauty and identity does not come from a relationship status, body size or what peers do or don't say. the standard of who we truly are..from the deepest and most authentic place, comes from a standard higher than the words of man. it comes from the lord. today as i encouraged the young girl, i was challenged to remember that for myself.

text:
swimming with the whales in tonga was a dream. 🐋 
but getting sexually assaulted just hours of arriving in this country was any traveller’s nightmare. 
it was also my reality.
i’ve got a new post on the blog today sharing my experience, and more importantly, trying to open up the discussion between traveller vs tourist. 
see, as a travel writer and ‘influencer’ i often feel pressured to go the local route rather than the easy, tourist one. most of the time i love the outcome and get some great experiences and stories. but in tonga, trying to blend with the locals backfired with a pretty awful outcome. 
somehow travel has become a contest to be the bravest/boldest/ most daring. but, at the end of the day, is your safety really worth the risk? after my experience, i’d say no. 
if you have five minutes i’d love for you to give the article a read (blog url in profile- it’s the latest article, under the slideshow) and let me know what you think. .
.

text:
den 12:e april i år avgick sara danius från sin post som svenska akademiens ständige sekreterare. veckan var häktisk, där nästan alla nyheter handlade om kaoset på svenska akademien. varför avgick katarina frostenson trots att akademien röstade kvar henne? vad har kulturprofilen jean-claude arnault med detta att göra? vad händer nu? det var många obesvarade frågor i luften, samtidigt som demonstrationer där folk klädde sig i knytblus hölls i olika delar av landet — för att folket ville visa sitt stöd för sara danius.
.
det som hände egentligen var resultatet av olika händelser; en läcka om nobelpriset, granskning om de 1,3 miljoner kronor som överförts till inofficiellt föreningskonto samt anklagelser och vittnesmål om  sexuella övergrepp och trakasserier i samband med #metoo. det sistnämnda blev väldigt uppmärksammat: 18 olika kvinnor vittnade nämligen om att den s.k. kulturprofilen (som har nära band till akademien, bl.a. pga hans fru som är akademiledamot). svenska akademien besvarade vittnesmålen med att avbryta allt samarbete med mannens kulturscen. sara danius berättar om att hon själv har fått skamliga förslag av kulturprofilen, vilket fick 8 kvinnor att polisanmäla honom, men förundersökningen lades ned några månader senare. hans fru, katarina frostenson, misstänks för partiskhet (jäv). när katarina fick fortsätta sitta kvar i akademien, valde flera personer att avgå i protest. sara danius kritiserade akademien och menade att stadgarna måste ändras så att reglerna för jäv och sekretess skärpas. även nobelkommittén kritiserade akademien hårt pga hur kulturprofilen sedan 1996 avslöjat sju nobelpristagare i förtid. akademien ville att sara avgår, så det gjorde hon. dagen efter bar folk knytblus för att visa henne stöd.
.
idag döms kulturprofilen jean-claud till två års fängelse för våldtäkt. i domen gav kvinnan som anmält honom ett mycket trovärdigt intryck på tingsrätten under rättegången. bevisen bygger även på de sju vittnen som stödjer kvinnans berättelse samt en journalanteckning som hennes terapeut gjorde två veckor efter ena våldtäkten (av två). jean-claude däremot gjorde inget trovärdigt intryck på tingsrätten. #tnkvrt

text:
last night my husband and i had the privilege of attending the someone to tell it to annual gathering. grateful people shared in person and internationally via video how this organization has impacted their lives through compassionate listening as they navigated loss, illness, loneliness, abuse, self-acceptance, and coming out.

guest speaker sterling riethman delivered a powerful message about the power of compassionate listening. riethman is a recipient of the arthur ashe courage award for her leading voice in the #metoomovement  her story of redemption, hope, purpose, and ultimately beauty through her pain as a sexual abuse survivor is inspiring.

my nature is that of a problem solver. there is value in the ability to find solutions. often, however, there is no solution, or a problem is not ours to solve.

walking alongside people as they clarify a vision for their homes and lives requires listening. it takes time and courage to declutter, for some more than others. every person and home has a story to tell.

take time to #listen to someone today.

if you need a listening ear or want to learn more about the #compassionatelistening work of someone to tell it to visit someonetotellitto.org. 
@some1totellitto
@sterlingshea

last night my husband and i had the privilege of attending the someone to tell it to annual gathering. grateful people shared in person and internationally via video how this organization has impacted their lives through compassionate listening as they navigated loss, illness, loneliness, abuse, self-acceptance, and coming out.

guest speaker sterling riethman delivered a powerful message about the power of compassionate listening. riethman is a recipient of the arthur ashe courage award for her leading voice in the #metoomovement  her story of redemption, hope, purpose, and ultimately beauty through her pain as a sexual abuse survivor is inspiring.

my nature is that of a problem solver. there is value in the ability to find solutions. often, however, there is no solution, or a problem is not ours to solve.

walking alongside people as they clarify a vision for their homes and lives requires listening. it takes time and courage to declutter, for some more than others. every person and home has a story to tell.

take time to #listen to someone today.

if you need a listening ear or want to learn more about the #compassionatelistening work of someone to tell it to visit someonetotellitto.org. 
@some1totellitto
@sterlingshea

text:
nu är melika zakariaes bok äntligen ute! 
en modig och viktig bok om att inget är omöjligt. beställ och sprid den! "melika zakariae är en ung och framgångsrik entreprenör och allt hon bestämmer sig för tycks bli verklighet. hon har gjort sig ett namn som bloggare, fotograf, dj och sedan startat en egen tidning. men bakom framgången finns en svår kamp som inte syns på ytan.

i 8 diagnoser får vi följa melika som söker svar på frågor hon alltid ställt. sökandet tar sin början 1979 under en våldsam statskupp i iran, flera år innan hon själv föddes. melika berättar om föräldrarnas flykt till sverige, sin uppväxt där hon var utåtagerande och stökig, hade svårt att passa in men samtidigt var omtyckt och full av energi. under ytan doldes ett mörker som ledde till destruktiva beteenden, ångest och missbruk. till slut ledde allt till en kollaps där hon tappade lusten att leva. nere på botten, när allt var som mörkast, så kom också vändningen och en lång och tuff resa inleddes för att försöka förstå det hon så länge flytt ifrån. trots näthat, sexism och avundsjuka gav hon inte upp, utan fortsatte hela tiden framåt. 
melika zakariae berättar om sexuella övergrepp, om trauman från krig som går i arv, om att leva med åtta psykiatriska diagnoser och mot alla odds nå framgång och lycka." #8diagnoser #boktips #böcker #boktoppen #psykiskohälsa #ångest #övergrepp #inspiration #nyaböcker #sexuellaövergrepp #metoo

have you asked the women in your life how they're doing this week? regramm- the standards won’t be lowered and i’d like to take a tiny moment this morning to call out all the men in my life who like to text and talk to me — especially those that like to flirt with me —  but haven’t sent a single message checking in or asking if i’m okay. i know all the ladies on here can relate. i feel grateful that i’ve created such a community for myself that there *are* wonderful men sending support and asking after my heart — and every single one is either queer or a survivor themselves (and one who is neither but just the wokest). boys do better or we’ll literally stop dating you. (@thegirlfriendmanifesto)
.

text_retweet:
we’re in the middle of a cultural shift about the way we talk about sexual assault, harassment, and rape. we have basically realized that a lot of us have stories we don’t tell because they feel confusing, shameful, or uncategorizable. i have three such stories, and i will tell you two.

about five years ago after a doctor’s appointment, i found myself sobbing and shaking in my car, wondering if a physical that i did not want should have involved the doctor’s hand inside of me. for context, i’d gone in with a skin problem that went undiagnosed for two more years because i did not want to see a doctor ever again. i called a good friend and told a pastor. both said something along the lines of it sucks that these things happen, but unfortunately this is the world we live in. 
two weeks ago, i had a violent nonconsentual encounter that left me at a loss. what do you call it when you are on a date that turns terrifying? when you know that the safest choice is to first endure and then escape? this time though, when i told a trusted member of my community, he suggested i report my experience. because it had not even occurred to me, i realized i had a job too, to hold people who cause harm accountable and share stories when i can even when they are painful, confusing, and embarrassing. the reason it is called the #metoo movement is because assault, harassment, and rape aren’t individual isolated crimes, they are a cultural problem, and as members of this culture, if you haven’t been affected directly there’s a close to 100% chance you know someone who has. one step towards change is reframing what is normal and what we will endure. i am sharing this not because i am proud (really there are so many things i wish i had done differently in both situations) but because maybe it will help you feel less alone or find words for what has happened to you. it is time to build a world where this isn’t something that just happens. enough. 
this is a repost from @ggastevich, who is making this line of sweet shirts and posters to support the national sexual assault survivors hotline. #believesurvivors #imwithher #drford #stopkavanaugh #timesup #metoo
name: Liz Vukelich

prompt word for today is "poisonous". people talk about others being toxic when it's more that behaviours and aspects of culture are toxic. there's plenty of reasons i never reported  being raped, dealing with other types of domestic abuse, or even self-defense to the authorities. the world needs to stop silencing and start listening to all victims of abuse, especially women and queer folks.

text:
am i merely a shadow of myself? 
no. 
light has no shadow.
the light from my eyes illuminates the cavernous sockets 
my skull shines 
but sockets are not just defined by the watchful light of my eyes
but too the shadows creeping on soft edges. 
the men whose eyes
imagined me 
their hands
reaching to touch me
their curled lip:
desperate,
angry,
predatory,
blowing out their light
trying to take mine
to kill me if necessary for this little light of mine
their eyes darkening
catcalling a pet
wanting to taste my flesh
predatory
hiding in shadows
where they can blend in
my skin has grown spikes 
with every new shed
shedding off the darkness:
the dusty, 
the molasses,
the suffocation,
letting water roll from the light in my eyes 
to rinse off 
old flesh
i am not a shadow of myself. 
no.
i am a light
trying to evade the shadows.
finding the things that rebound rainbows back inside
celebrating flowers, bees, puppies, cheese
dancing 
a warrior dance
with fellow warriors; fellow empaths; fellow metoos
becoming softer inside to allow more light 
harder outside 
a tree who can sway in the wind but whose bark is dense.
a tree whose roots dance deeper 
a tree whose branches celebrate higher
a necessary adaptation
i am filled with light
i am light.
•
•

text:
2018 cp of nys annual conference

sexual harassment – the allegations are serious, so your investigation must be as well
richard d. landau, esq., shareholder, jackson lewis p.c.

as the #metoo movement impacts virtually every workplace, many organizations are asking themselves about what they can do to change their cultures but also, how they can address the misdeeds of the past which are alleged by staff in the present. from a liability perspective, the answer lies in the investigation. many of the recent headlines do contain horrific allegations but the key component creating liability is the failure to investigate well and act quickly. this discussion will focus on the hallmarks of consistent, thorough, fair and swift investigations which by extension signal an organization’s deep commitment to effectively addressing sexual harassment in the workplace.

text:
'back off' #metoo - apart from the multiple other instances i've had, this needed voice

given the literate surroundings, if you thought urban mindsets were different from the rural, it's shattering for me to break to you that it's not much different.

women are still 'objects' (some maybe of desire, some maybe just for the sheer fun of anatomy dissection) for the pleasure of others - (men & yes, devastatingly, other women too). when the causal & so-called 'harmless', 'just-checking-out' takes a new form.

maybe owing to how we are conditioned growing up as indian children, but that, will never be a justification that's good enough.

only distinction i can think of between the urban and rural men is that the course of action they adopt. a rural boy will chase the simpleton to rip her choli apart. the urban guy is supposedly informed & civil, but sadly with the same mindset.

the action of rape is a crime, but the virtual pleasure isn't, right? he would hence, not rape her through actions, but will also not think twice before visually molesting her.
doesn't this still qualify as sexually harassment too?

while we know objectification of a person - (woman or man, yes why exclude him?) is downright wrong, but making jokes about it is okay, right? the excuse that it's just in plain humour!

shaming someone for something they have absolutely no control over, calling names like small penis or big boobs or tiny melons is not funny. it is just not a subject matter to joke about. no.

it's so sad that when people run out of topics to enjoy their general banter, discussing people's bodies comes to the rescue to become the laughing stock.

ludicrous to understand that these otherwise 'so-smart minds', cannot understand the grave repercussions this can have for someone they were 'so-generally' joking about.

it's at the cost of someone's self-esteem, making them conscious of their own bodies, spiralling mental complexes, leaving them deeply underconfident in their own skin. throwing them into a never-ending trench of identity crisis, pushing them to get stuck in the vicious trap of depression which can be life-threatening. it is just not funny.

read in the comment below.

text:
“let your own story and journey be what you want it to be and know that it’s ok.”
••
how i’ve dealt with things in my past was by trying to act as if they didn’t happen, avoiding talking about it, and withdrawing.
but, lately i’ve been uncovering these things, opening up to being vulnerable, and beginning/continuing the process of healing.
••
my story and journey is me, it is what makes me me, is what has lead me to this point in my life, and is what is driving me forward to not only help and heal myself but to in turn pay that forward.
••
my theme lately has been change.✨
previously, change was so scary to me.. i didn’t like taking chances, i didn’t like the thought of possible failure and disappointment, i didn’t like the thought of maybe getting hurt in the process of doing what was best for myself..
••
i have since then learned that i am not alone. i am a strong woman who is capable of handling pain, anxiety, depression, and overcoming it. i will never discount other people’s pain or act as if it is an easy process because i know that is far from the truth, even for myself.
••
i am however, actively trying my best to become my best. i am tired of living a life where i don’t like who i am. where i don’t like where i’ve been or where i’m headed.. i cannot change the past, or how i have acted or reacted. but, i can change my future and how i do things, how i look at the world, at myself, and make my life be how i want it to be. 🌻
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
“my pre-arrival research had revealed a promising (though rough) notion: that a city that gave the first land grant to a woman in 1798, formed a greater cleveland congress in support of international women’s year in 1975, and houses the international women’s air & space museum might be an intriguing place to explore what territories — literal and metaphorical — women occupied. my interest in this notion intensified as i read one #metoo article after another. over the course of my residency, i talked with more than a dozen artists, curators, and arts administrators, all of them identifying as women or non-binary.”

text: all of the stories coming out from people who have been raped/sexually assaulted and never reported it are, simultaneously, breaking my heart, and giving me hope. to everyone, men, women, and children, alike, that have been too ashamed to come forward until now, i believe you and i’m so so so sorry that you were violated. i’m so so so proud of you for finding the courage to speak up now. it is never the fault of the victim. being wasted, wearing revealing clothing, flirting, walking alone at night, laying in someone’s bed, even walking around completely naked is not an invitation for rape/sexual assault. it’s ok to be afraid to talk about it. it’s ok to feel ashamed, even though it wasn’t your fault. please know that i am here and i believe you. please know that i will listen. i will cry with you. i will defend you and advocate for you. from one survivor to another, you never deserved what happened. please know that you are loved! #metoo #hertoo #himtoo #themtoo

text:
happy october 👻 monthly reading for the collective🎃 
wow! lots of flying cards today. this reading is about the divine feminine rising. this month, will be a fast track of what the divine feminine has been trying to accomplish in the last 18 months. 🔥 there will be some major growing pains here, but nothing we can shift and turn into a positive aspect. so much low vibe, gossip, he said she said while  i woman coming forward, anonymous or not, with their stories of of sexual assault. why are we judging someones story (page of wands/queen of swords). is this your place to have an opinion? i can see perpetrators trying to sneak away, and get away with it, but soft whispers will be turning into shrill screams, and society and the divine masculine can’t ignore them anymore. i’m see joining together in community with support, and love. where there was shame, it will be replaced with cries of #metoo. now there is a shift happening for the divine masculine to the divine feminine and it will be off kilter, it  be raw... and untamed. for now we need to focus on balance. i am not speaking of male vs female here, i’m talking the actual energy, the ying and yang. we are both the masculine and the feminine. instead of trying to over rule one or the other, we need to seek purity and healing for both. i am being told that what is happening here on earth is a small taste of what is changing in the spirit realm. it’s gonna feel rocky for now... and that’s okay. we also have to acknowledge not sending energy towards hate, but instead sending it towards the collectives reprogramming. it’s coming one way or another.... you can either go with or against the current. the choice is yours. choose love over all. for the feminine collective has had a slow steady climb, and the divine masculine is getting a body slam this month. 🎃 i’ve never had a reading like this before. all i know is there will be a big shift! and that’s beautiful. be gentle on one another. truth is coming ✨#moonlightsapothecary #tarot #october #divinefeminine #divinemasculine

text:
بعد أن تمّ إصدار حُكم بالسّجن مُدة قد تصل إلى 10 سنوات، بحق الممثل العالمي "بيل كوزبي"، نتيجة اغتصابه أكثر من امرأة في العقد الماضي، تستمر فضائح تحرّش النّجوم بالتّكشف واحدة تلو الآخرى، خصوصاً بعد إطلاق حملة #metoo التي تُحارب التّحرّش.

ويُعد أسطورة كُرة القدم "كريستيانو رونالدو" آخر الأسماء التي أدرجت في قائمة المُتحرّشين، بعد أن اتّهمته امرأة تُدعى "كاثرين مايورغا" أنّه تحرّش بها في عام 2009، عندما كانت تقضي وقتها في أحد فنادق لاس فيغاس التي كان يُقيم بها كريستيانو.

وفي تفاصيل القّصة التي كشفت عنها كاثرين لمجلة der spiegel الألمانية، صرّحت بأنّ رونالدو دعاها إلى غُرفته الخّاصة، وطلب منها مُمارسة علاقة حميمة معه، فرفضت ذلك، وما كان منه إلّا أن اغتصبها.

واستطردت مايورغا في لقائها مع المجلّة، أنّه بعد انتهاء رونالدو من فعلته الشّنيعة، اعتذر لها قائلاً: "أنا رجلٌ صالح 99 بالمئة، لكن ليس لدي علمٌ بشأن الواحد بالمئة المُتبقيّة". وبعدما انتشرت فضيحة رونالدو كالنّار في الهشيم في أوساط الإنترنت، خرج لاعب ريال مدريد السّابق عن صمته، وعلّق على تصريحات مايورغا عبر خاصية البث المُباشر في إنستغرامه، ووصفها بالمُزيّفة، وكُل ما تُريده هذه السّيدة استغلال اسمه من أجل الشّهرة.
ومن ناحية القضاء، سيرفع مُحامي رونالدو دعوى قضائية ضد المجلة الألمانية، بالإضافة إلى دفاعهم عن موكّلهم في القضية التي رفعتها عليه كاثرين.

أمّا من جهة حبيبته، فدعمت جورجينا رودريغز حبيبها رونالدو عبر صورةٍ نشرتها في إنستغرامها، إذ ظهرت في أحد الملاعب التي كان يتدرّب فيها حبيبها، وعلّقت عليها: "دائماً ما تُحوّل العقبات إلى مصدر قوّة لكي تُبيّن مدى روعتك. شكراً لأنك تجعلنا نستمتع في كُل مُباراة، أتمنى لك الأفضل في المُستقبل. أحبك يا كريستيانو". #حليمة_بولند #مي_العيدان #روجينا #سما_المصري #افلام_عربيه #افلام_اكشن #صور #سينما #العاصمة #مي_عمر #صافيناز #الجونة_السينمائي #مصر #دراما #ترندينغ #ترند #movies #art #صبا_مبارك #فن #الفن_السابع #هوليود #بوليود #أبداع #مجلة_الحصيلة_الفنية #قناة_الحصيلة #صحيفة_الحصيلة #اليوم_السابع #شنينة
name: صحيفة الحصيلة الإلكترونية

text:
5 years ago today i was officially out of an abusive relationship. honestly, i’m still embarrassed to talk about it. but i celebrate this day so hard every year to remind myself that i am enough, and worth it, and in control. for any man that has told you it’s your fault, or said that you pushed them to that point, or made you feel less than, f*ck you. but today, celebrate if you survived, and if you’re in a bad place, know that things will get better, that you can get out, that there are people out there willing and wanting to be there for you. 💖💖💖💖💖💖

text:
part 1
i have a different video coming this sunday. i have held my breathe in for almost 7 years just to say #metoo. this is the hardest thing i will ever have to face. and you’re right, i don’t have to face it on social media. but the thing is i’m not facing it on social media. i’m facing it in my heart, like i have for 7 years. this is only the beginning. the only thing i want to come from this is support, and knowing i can help at least one woman, young or old. i will explain everything. what happened and what didn’t happen, why i did or didn’t say anything, and how i feel now. if you think this is a bandwagon video... please, do not interact with me at all in regards to my truth, and wait on a happy video next weekend. i love you guys. xoxo

text:
last week was heavy. 
if you watched the testimonies of dr. ford and b. kavanaugh, you may have cringed, listened in disbelief (of his behavior while responding), and shocked at details of the incident.

we believe her and it is important that we change the narriatve when women (and men) are assaulted and stay silent. we have to protect each other. we have to raise children to be respectful & compassionate people with discipline and self control. 
this isn't about "why is she telling now?". this is about a man up for nomination into a lifelong position that affects citizens of the united states. his views on issues (esp those of women) have to be considered and questioned. 
if one cannot go with an open mind and leave their personal values and/or party affiliation out when making a decision, the supreme court judge seat is not for you. 
we stand with women. we see the character of a man/woman. we speak truth. we speak up. we support what's right, even when others are against it. we stand for justice.

#uprisingexperience #stopkavanaugh #webelieveyou #metoo #supremecourt #speakup #kavanaugh #politics #riseup #takeaseat #shiftinpower #power

text: #metoo i am a survivor. i was around this age when my babysitter’s boyfriend assaulted me. the trauma of these memories was stored in my body, in my character, my strength and defiance of any person who invaded my personal space. i never let another person touch me without consent again. i became a fighter. i learned martial arts in my youth and boxing as a young woman working in the alcohol industry. i walked alone in the streets of every major us city as a brand manager, as a woman. i never feared an attack. i always felt safe because i knew that i would never allow that kind of energy into my life again. about 7 years ago i started having vivid dreams about the assault i survived as a toddler. i have never spoken publicly about what happened. i didn’t remember what happened for more than 20 years. i believe survivors and i am grateful to all the people who have come forward and told their stories. abuse is cyclical. i imagined my abuser probably suffered a similar trauma. the only way to heal, to reconcile is to acknowledge and atone for the past. we are not what happened to us. we are what we choose to become. self love is the only way to end this behaviour. when people love themselves there is no room for hate. there is no room for a continued cycle of oppression and abuse. we must stand up and change how we are with ourselves and each other. i am a survivor. i am a woman. i am human. i am love. i am an innocent soul and so are you. take responsibility and let us work as a whole to end the suffering of so many innocent souls. today is a new day and tomorrow will be forever changed by the courage of those willing to come forward and stand up for what is right. lastly, to the little girl in this photo, i love you, i will always protect you, you are innocent and in the depths of my caring heart, you are free.

tweet_full: #metoo i am a survivor. i was around this age when my babysitter’s boyfriend assaulted me. the trauma of these memories was stored in my body, in my character, my strength and defiance of any person who invaded my personal space. i never let another person touch me without consent again. i became a fighter. i learned martial arts in my youth and boxing as a young woman working in the alcohol industry. i walked alone in the streets of every major us city as a brand manager, as a woman. i never feared an attack. i always felt safe because i knew that i would never allow that kind of energy into my life again. about 7 years ago i started having vivid dreams about the assault i survived as a toddler. i have never spoken publicly about what happened. i didn’t remember what happened for more than 20 years. i believe survivors and i am grateful to all the people who have come forward and told their stories. abuse is cyclical. i imagined my abuser probably suffered a similar trauma. the only way to heal, to reconcile is to acknowledge and atone for the past. we are not what happened to us. we are what we choose to become. self love is the only way to end this behaviour. when people love themselves there is no room for hate. there is no room for a continued cycle of oppression and abuse. we must stand up and change how we are with ourselves and each other. i am a survivor. i am a woman. i am human. i am love. i am an innocent soul and so are you. take responsibility and let us work as a whole to end the suffering of so many innocent souls. today is a new day and tomorrow will be forever changed by the courage of those willing to come forward and stand up for what is right. lastly, to the little girl in this photo, i love you, i will always protect you, you are innocent and in the depths of my caring heart, you are free.

text:
män motverkar gemensamt strukturer
– alla män är i princip delaktiga i att upprätthålla den struktur som leder till mäns våld. därför måste vi män gemensamt förändra den.
så säger henrik perälä, som kom till en samtalskväll på mäns samtalsturné "#eftermetoo" när den hade ett stopp i norrköping förra veckan. han var väldigt nöjd med kvällen i helhet, och förvånad över den självklara öppenheten i samtalen:
– det säger en del om vad man är van vid.
så vad kan män göra för att gemensamt förändra dessa strukturer? skriv dina förslag i kommentarerna nedan!
#eftermetoo #allamän #metoo #postkodseffekten #projektförförändring @postkodstiftelsen

text:
maybe there was something in the @thombrowneny show notes we didn't see, but we're finding it hard to grasp the need to show women literally bound and gagged on the runway at this particular moment in time.  in an era where women’s accusations are consistently doubted and dissected at every step, this showing reads as tone deaf.  if this was somehow a response to end the silencing of women, it missed the mark.  between their models incapacitated by the 5 inch heels (many with their arms laced down, unable to brace a potential tumble), the near vaj-exposing finale parade at saint laurent, and hedi slimane obliterating any shred of the thoughtful sensitivity that phoebe philo imbued into women's fashion at @celine , paris fashion week seems to be on shaky ground.  at least we still have miuccia to save the day with @miumiu tomorrow.  besides all that, how about that tribute to anna della russo in her heyday of streetstyle stardom? lol. •

text:
(idk why my vids keep loading sideways) #randomthoughts on #metoo and the incessant defense of raping rapists who rape by men and  who want to give sexual assailants more benefit of the doubt than those who have been assailed. 
i tend to forget that there is a common cultural practice within many males to supress their experience of trauma and/or find retribution by playing out their trauma physically (fighting, working, having sex) 
the means to gain respect amongst many men, is not to identify why you are inherently worth respect, but to assert dominance. 
girls are commonly conditioned (culturally and societally) to "earn" respect through service and submission. not dominance. 
it is why we are consistantly at an impasse when we try to communicate our most vulnerable experiences. 
many men believe they are in control of their outcomes until they aren't. and when they aren't, it's because they failed and no one is going to be there to lick their wounds but their moms and the women they lay in bed with. men are used to having to suffer in private while women and girls are encouraged to emote. 
i believe men subconsciously envy these safe spaces believed to be built exclusive of them.

i'm telling you now, it's not. you are just as welcome to find sanctuary. find it. before you play your pain  out (passively or aggressively, consciously or unconciously, intentionally or unintentionally)  on somebody else.

she takes the stand 
with the voice of millions on her back
and speaks the fact that we all know, 
far too well to be true -  me too.

she is heard with faith deceived .

when will it be enough -
is one in six not enough ?
is one sister, one friend 
still - not enough?

one colleague, one mother, one wife, one lover -
one teacher, one doctor, one preacher, one author -
one husband, one son, one brother.

the non-consensual clock 
and make us realise that -

time. is. up. #metoo #she #woman #dreamcatchers #iseeyou

text:
the hearing on thursday got me thinking a lot about my own experiences and the culture around male friendship. misogyny is dangerous for everyone. it strips men of responsibility and treats them as though they are animals, incapable of controlling themselves. it pressures them into harming others in exchange for social status. it strips women of autonomy. it holds them down and keeps them silent and subservient, unable to wield their power to change the world. it teaches children to go against their instincts to love and respect all people equally. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this culture is dangerous and it is painful. so many of us want to speak out, want to scream, but we don’t know how because we’ve been taught all our lives that our voices cannot be trusted. silence is safety because saying no can get you killed. silence is safety because speaking out brings death threats. many of us can’t take those risks. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this hearing brought back a lot of pain and fear for many people and i just want to say, i see you. i see you making your voice heard in whatever way is safest for you. i see you reaching out, silently screaming.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
بعد أن تمّ إصدار حُكم بالسّجن مُدة قد تصل إلى 10 سنوات، بحق الممثل العالمي #بيل_كوزبي  نتيجة اغتصابه أكثر من امرأة في العقد الماضي، تستمر فضائح تحرّش النّجوم بالتّكشف واحدة تلو الآخرى، خصوصاً بعد إطلاق حملة #metoo التي تُحارب التّحرّش.

ويُعد أسطورة كُرة القدم #كريستيانو_رونالدو  آخر الأسماء التي أدرجت في قائمة المُتحرّشين، بعد أن اتّهمتهاتهمت عارضة أزياء أمريكية سابقة تُدعى #كاثرين_مايورغا  أنّه تحرّش بها في عام 2009، عندما كانت تقضي وقتها في أحد فنادق لاس فيغاس التي كان يُقيم بها كريستيانو.

ادعت "كاثرين مايورغا"، وهي معلمة تبلغ من العمر 34 عامًا كانت تطمح لأن تكون عارضة أزياء وقت الهجوم المزعوم، أن "كريستيانو رونالدو" أقدم على اغتصابها في حمام فندق وكازينو بالمز في لاس فيغاس في ساعات الصباح الأولى من تاريخ 13 يونيو 2009.

ووفق ما نقله موقع "ديلي ميل" البريطاني حول وقائع الحادثة المشينة، فقد التقى "كريستيانو" بـ"كاثرين" في نادي rain الليلي في بالمز ، وتظهر الصور لقطة حميمية يُمسِك فيها النجم يد الضحية ويهمس في أذنها ببضع كلمات، ثم يدعوها هي وأصدقائها إلى جناحه الفندقي من أجل الاستمتاع بمنظر لاس فيغاس ستريب.

وفي أوراق المحكمة، زعمت "كاثرين" رفضها طلب النجم بالدخول إلى حوض الاستحمام الساخن كي لا تتلف ملابسها، عندها قرر "كريستيانو" إعطائها ملابس رياضية وطلب منها التوجه للحمام لتبديل ملابسها، في تلك اللحظة دخل عليها فجأة وهو عاري الجسد وطلب منها أداء بعض الحركات الجنسية أمامه.
ورغم توسلات "كاثرين" لإطلاق سراحها، ألقاها النجم نحو السرير واغتصبها  وبعد انتهاء رونالدو من فعلته ، اعتذر لها قائلاً: "أنا رجلٌ صالح 99 بالمئة، لكن ليس لدي علمٌ بشأن الواحد بالمئة المُتبقيّة". وبعدما انتشرت فضيحة رونالدو كالنّار في الهشيم في أوساط الإنترنت، خرج لاعب ريال مدريد السّابق عن صمته، وعلّق على تصريحات مايورغا عبر خاصية البث المُباشر في إنستغرامه، ووصفها بالمُزيّفة، وكُل ما تُريده هذه السّيدة استغلال اسمه من أجل الشّهرة.

ومن ناحية القضاء، سيرفع مُحامي رونالدو دعوى قضائية ضد المجلة الألمانية، بالإضافة إلى دفاعهم عن موكّلهم في القضية التي رفعتها عليه كاثرين.

أمّا من جهة حبيبته، فدعمت جورجينا رودريغز حبيبها رونالدو عبر صورةٍ نشرتها في إنستغرامها، إذ ظهرت في أحد الملاعب التي كان يتدرّب فيها حبيبها، وعلّقت عليها: "دائماً ما تُحوّل العقبات إلى مصدر قوّة لكي تُبيّن مدى روعتك. شكراً لأنك تجعلنا نستمتع في كُل مُباراة، أتمنى لك الأفضل في المُستقبل. أحبك يا كريستيانو".
.

ويُعد أسطورة كُرة القدم #كريستيانو_رونالدو  آخر الأسماء التي أدرجت في قائمة المُتحرّشين، بعد أن اتّهمتهاتهمت عارضة أزياء أمريكية سابقة تُدعى #كاثرين_مايورغا  أنّه تحرّش بها في عام 2009، عندما كانت تقضي وقتها في أحد فنادق لاس فيغاس التي كان يُقيم بها كريستيانو.

ادعت "كاثرين مايورغا"، وهي معلمة تبلغ من العمر 34 عامًا كانت تطمح لأن تكون عارضة أزياء وقت الهجوم المزعوم، أن "كريستيانو رونالدو" أقدم على اغتصابها في حمام فندق وكازينو بالمز في لاس فيغاس في ساعات الصباح الأولى من تاريخ 13 يونيو 2009.

ووفق ما نقله موقع "ديلي ميل" البريطاني حول وقائع الحادثة المشينة، فقد التقى "كريستيانو" بـ"كاثرين" في نادي rain الليلي في بالمز ، وتظهر الصور لقطة حميمية يُمسِك فيها النجم يد الضحية ويهمس في أذنها ببضع كلمات، ثم يدعوها هي وأصدقائها إلى جناحه الفندقي من أجل الاستمتاع بمنظر لاس فيغاس ستريب.

وفي أوراق المحكمة، زعمت "كاثرين" رفضها طلب النجم بالدخول إلى حوض الاستحمام الساخن كي لا تتلف ملابسها، عندها قرر "كريستيانو" إعطائها ملابس رياضية وطلب منها التوجه للحمام لتبديل ملابسها، في تلك اللحظة دخل عليها فجأة وهو عاري الجسد وطلب منها أداء بعض الحركات الجنسية أمامه.
ورغم توسلات "كاثرين" لإطلاق سراحها، ألقاها النجم نحو السرير واغتصبها  وبعد انتهاء رونالدو من فعلته ، اعتذر لها قائلاً: "أنا رجلٌ صالح 99 بالمئة، لكن ليس لدي علمٌ بشأن الواحد بالمئة المُتبقيّة". وبعدما انتشرت فضيحة رونالدو كالنّار في الهشيم في أوساط الإنترنت، خرج لاعب ريال مدريد السّابق عن صمته، وعلّق على تصريحات مايورغا عبر خاصية البث المُباشر في إنستغرامه، ووصفها بالمُزيّفة، وكُل ما تُريده هذه السّيدة استغلال اسمه من أجل الشّهرة.

ومن ناحية القضاء، سيرفع مُحامي رونالدو دعوى قضائية ضد المجلة الألمانية، بالإضافة إلى دفاعهم عن موكّلهم في القضية التي رفعتها عليه كاثرين.

أمّا من جهة حبيبته، فدعمت جورجينا رودريغز حبيبها رونالدو عبر صورةٍ نشرتها في إنستغرامها، إذ ظهرت في أحد الملاعب التي كان يتدرّب فيها حبيبها، وعلّقت عليها: "دائماً ما تُحوّل العقبات إلى مصدر قوّة لكي تُبيّن مدى روعتك. شكراً لأنك تجعلنا نستمتع في كُل مُباراة، أتمنى لك الأفضل في المُستقبل. أحبك يا كريستيانو".
.

بعد إطلاق حملة التي تُحارب التّحرّش . ويُعد أسطورة كُرة القدم آخر الأسماء التي أدرجت في قائمة المُتحرّشين، بعد أن اتّهمتهاتهمت عارضة أزياء أمريكية سابقة تُدعى أنّه تحرّش بها في عام 2009، عندما كانت تقضي وقتها في أحد فنادق لاس فيغاس التي كان يُقيم بها كريستيانو . ادعت `` كاثرين مايورغا '' ، وهي معلمة تبلغ من العمر 34 عامًا كانت تطمح لأن تكون عارضة أزياء وقت الهجوم المزعوم، أن `` كريستيانو رونالدو '' أقدم على اغتصابها في حمام فندق وكازينو بالمز في لاس فيغاس في ساعات الصباح الأولى من تاريخ 13 يونيو 2009 . ووفق ما نقله موقع `` ديلي ميل '' البريطاني حول وقائع الحادثة المشينة، فقد التقى `` كريستيانو '' بـ '' كاثرين '' في نادي rain الليلي في بالمز ، وتظهر الصور لقطة حميمية يُمسِك فيها النجم يد الضحية ويهمس في أذنها ببضع كلمات، ثم يدعوها هي وأصدقائها إلى جناحه الفندقي من أجل الاستمتاع بمنظر لاس فيغاس ستريب . وفي أوراق المحكمة، زعمت `` كاثرين '' رفضها طلب النجم بالدخول إلى حوض الاستحمام الساخن كي لا تتلف ملابسها، عندها قرر `` كريستيانو '' إعطائها ملابس رياضية وطلب منها التوجه للحمام لتبديل ملابسها، في تلك اللحظة دخل عليها فجأة وهو عاري الجسد وطلب منها أداء بعض الحركات الجنسية أمامه . ورغم توسلات `` كاثرين '' لإطلاق سراحها، ألقاها النجم نحو السرير واغتصبها وبعد انتهاء رونالدو من فعلته ، اعتذر لها قائلاً : `` أنا رجلٌ صالح 99 بالمئة، لكن ليس لدي علمٌ بشأن الواحد بالمئة المُتبقيّة '' . وبعدما انتشرت فضيحة رونالدو كالنّار في الهشيم في أوساط الإنترنت، خرج لاعب ريال مدريد السّابق عن صمته، وعلّق على تصريحات مايورغا عبر خاصية البث المُباشر في إنستغرامه، ووصفها بالمُزيّفة، وكُل ما تُريده هذه السّيدة استغلال اسمه من أجل الشّهرة . ومن ناحية القضاء، سيرفع مُحامي رونالدو دعوى قضائية ضد المجلة الألمانية، بالإضافة إلى دفاعهم عن موكّلهم في القضية التي رفعتها عليه كاثرين . أمّا من جهة حبيبته، فدعمت جورجينا رودريغز حبيبها رونالدو عبر صورةٍ نشرتها في إنستغرامها، إذ ظهرت في أحد الملاعب التي كان يتدرّب فيها حبيبها، وعلّقت عليها : `` دائماً ما تُحوّل العقبات إلى مصدر قوّة لكي تُبيّن مدى روعتك . شكراً لأنك تجعلنا نستمتع في كُل مُباراة، أتمنى لك الأفضل في المُستقبل . أحبك يا كريستيانو '' . .

text:
it's october!
our monthly dancer only meeting is coming up quick!
october 15th from 4 til 6 pm
in downtown springfield ma

transportation and childcare available with advance notice

our topic this month is sexual assault
whether in or out of the club whether recent or long ago
we believe survivors.

share your story in a safe space with colleagues and fellow dancers.
we will have advocates from the local ywca as well as legal counsel from the victims rights law center
theyll let us know what resources they have available for us ranging from
free legal help free counselling help with emergency housing even help taking care of your pets while you heal from trauma and get yourself some help.
walking you through the legal process and even resoyrces for folks who can not or do not want to seek legal recourse.

free hot meal provided!

come join us!
dm or email for location and more info

teamclearheels413@protonmail.com

#ibelieveyou
#metoo #survivors #teamclearheels413
#teamclearheels #dancersonly #413 #westernmass #ywca #vrlc #victimsrights #victimsrightslawcenter #yesastripper

text:
bill cosby, la caída de un ídolo al que todos amaban
fama. el comediante llegó a ser la estrella mejor pagada de la televisión. hoyo. ahora cayó en la lista de depredador sexual de ee.uu

los angeles.-bill cosby está parado ante el juez steven o’neill en el tribunal de pensilvania, esperando el veredicto que lo llevará por varios años a la cárcel a los 81 años. 35 mujeres aseguraron públicamente que él las drogó y las violó, o que abusó de ellas.

pero solo andrea constand logró llevarlo a juicio luego de años de litigios y una condena ejemplar. su caso fue el primero y el más resonante de la era #metoo que denuncia acoso sexuales en el mundo de hollywood.

el hombre que está escuchando al juez, bien trajeado y con una mirada apacible, hasta cálida, fue alguna vez el ídolo máximo de la televisión estadounidense, que ahora ha caído en desgracia.

text:
tw// sexual assault references
•
“it’s no big deal, it’s just a touch”
“it’s no big deal, boys will be boys”
“it’s no big deal, it was years ago. you should be over it by now”
“it’s no big deal, but you’ll wreck their future if you tell”

stop.
stop the excuses, stop the normalization.
stop the victim blaming.

stop saying “it’s no big deal, everyone does it. this happens all the time.”— start saying that things have to change.

stop saying “boys will be boys”—
start realizing will be held accountable for their actions, no matter how long ago it happened.

stop saying, “it’ll ruin his future.”—
start thinking about the victim and their future. their recovery. their pain.

dr. ford’s story is by no means an isolated one.
almost every woman, and quite a few men, that i know can share their experiences like hers.

stand with survivors and against their abusers.

if you stand with kavanaugh, unfollow me now. ••

text:
in the past few weeks i’ve been verbally abuse. that made me think where are we standing as a society: men assuming that publishing a photo wearing a bikini makes you a whore and women attacking with offensive comments.
the human body is beautiful, it’s the perfect machine and i don’t get it, why most of the time we make it a taboo.
i’m sick of feeling bad with myself and my body, people calling me: fatass, mamacita or a hoe. like if i stopped being a human being and transforming myself into an adjective.
today i say enough is enough! i love myself, i love my body, i am not and object and will never be your object. ••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• en las últimas semanas he sido víctima de  mucho acoso. eso me hizo pensar mucho en donde estamos parados como sociedad: hombres que piensan que al subir una foto en bikini eres fácil y mujeres atacando con adjetivos ofensivos.
el cuerpo humano es hermoso, es una máquina perfecta y no entiendo porque la mayoría de las veces lo objetivisamos. 
estoy cansada de sentirme mal con y por mi cuerpo, que me llamen: buena, mamacita o zorra. como sí dejase de ser una persona para volverme un adjetivo. ¡hoy digo basta! me amo y amo mi cuerpo, no soy un objeto, no soy tu objeto.

text:
hey instagram, it’s been a minute. a lot of my art has fallen to the wayside this year for a myriad of reasons, but i’m taking this moment and #inktober as an opportunity to get back in the game. 
this year i’m not following the prompt list. instead, i decided to focus on activists—patrons and patriots who worked hard to make life better for a lot of people. 
originally, dr. ford wasn’t on my list, but after watching her testimony last thursday i couldn’t stop thinking about her, her bravery, and the millions of women who have been sexually harassed, abused, or raped. because of her more women are speaking up about their experiences, and more conversations are happening with friends, family, and coworkers. 
this is so incredibly important. she’s not the first woman to speak out, nor is she even the first to speak out against a supreme court nominee (a great thank you to you, #anitahill, for doing it first), but she is the one currently occupying the national consciousness and conscience. it is my sincere hope that her voice, and the voices of countless others who add their voices to hers, will propel the change required to acknowledge these abuses and the pain they cause, and seek a remedy.

#ibelieveher 
#inktober2018 #christineblaseyford #illustration #pen #penandink #penandinkdrawing #copic #copicart #stippling #stipple #dotart #dotwork #illustrator #illustrations #inkdrawing #drawing #sketch #art #artistsoninstagram #inkart #penart #sexualabuse #metoo #activist #blackworknow

text:
fuck trigger warnings ⚠️🖕
just hear me out for a sec and then we can have a conversation about our opinions...
i understand you're trying to protect me. you're doing your best not to hurt my feelings. to bring to the surface all the old memories that may be latched with your words. but you shouldn't have to protect me from your words. that is not the purpose of telling your truths. the purpose is to find camaraderie, for people to understand they aren't alone, maybe to prevent this from happening again. and i believe that trigger warnings deter from this vital message. 
hear me now...
throwing trigger warnings is like preemptively apologizing for what happened/destroyed/hurt you. you should never apologize/justify your actions!  not to me, not to your significant other, not to a politician,  not to society and especially not your attacker! this wasn't your fault. you should not carry that guilt, that shame.
this is like when someone says... 'not to be rude but...' and then they say something extremely rude. we need to stop for a moment and be honest with ourselves and with others.
i want to reshape everyones mindset. i want us to be strong, adult females and males. i want us to raise the next generation of strong adults. i want us to tell our truths and memoirs without judgement. .
if you continue to use trigger warnings i won't condemn you. but i will not use them on my page. i can only be unapologetically myself and i wish, no i want you to do the same. 
just think about it...please. actually i want thoughts and opinions on this. because you're either going to love or hate me after this post. the unfollow button is right there if you can hang with it 👆
.
i think it's time to bust up societies norm. to rise above. to stop hiding behind trigger warnings!
.
.
.
.

i understand you are trying to protect me. you are doing your best not to hurt my feelings. to bring to the surface all the old memories that may be latched with your words. but you should not have to protect me from your words. that is not the purpose of telling your truths. the purpose is to find camaraderie, for people to understand they are not alone, maybe to prevent this from happening again. and i believe that trigger warnings deter from this vital message. 
hear me now...
throwing trigger warnings is like preemptively apologizing for what happened/destroyed/hurt you. you should never apologize/justify your actions!  not to me, not to your significan not other, not to a politician,  not to society and especially not your attacker! this wasn't your fault. you should not carry that guilt, that shame.
this is like when someone says... 'not to be rude but...' and then they say something extremely rude. we need to stop for a moment and be honest with ourselves and with others.
i want to reshape everyones mindset. i want us to be strong, adult females and males. i want us to raise the next generation of strong adults. i want us to tell our truths and memoirs without judgement. .
if you continue to use trigger warnings i will not condemn you. but i will not use them on my page. i can only be unapologetically myself and i wish, no i want you to do the same. 
just think about it...please. actually i want thoughts and opinions on this. because you are either going to love or hate me after this post. the unfollow button is right there if you can hang with it 👆
.
i think it is time to bust up societies norm. to rise above. to stop hiding behind trigger warnings!
.
.
.
.

text:
consent part 6...
vanderbilt university conducted a survey in 2015 and reported that approximately 20% of undergraduate responders had experienced some form of  unwanted sexual contact. these numbers aren't shocking because sexual assault is so prevalent in our society, even amongst peer groups. as previously mentioned, the lack of discussion regarding consent can be attributed to some of the behaviors seen amongst peer groups, although that in no way excuses the behavior. one student reported that she had consented to intercourse with a classmate, but required that he wear a condom, which he agreed to do. after the sex ended, she discovered that he had not actually put the condom on. she immediately reported the incident and went to seek medical care. ultimately the school determined that a sexual assault had occurred because their student handbook specifically states that "effective consent requires mutual understanding and agreement regarding the use and/or method of prophylaxis and contraception.” if you are a college student or the parent of a college student, do you know what your school's policy is regarding consent and the use of prophylaxis and contraception? did you know you or your student could be found guilty of sexual assault by failing to adhere to the use of the agreed form of protection? understanding the concept of consent on every level is critical to ensuring that one does not become guilty of assault. it's time to have these conversations if you haven't done so!! #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #sexcrimes #rapevictims #rape #victims #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate

text: this week we’ve opened so many old wounds. so many scars we’ve buried have come to light. but this is only the beginning, it’s the light we need to expose the injustices we’ve faced. we’ve too often hidden in the shadows- shamed for our bodies, for our voices, for our opinions and self love. enough is enough- enough hiding, enough excuses, enough of the silence. speak your truth - find your strength and don’t be afraid to reach out to those around who who’ve also suffered silently.

text:
fifty-eight percent of female faculty and staff in academic institutions have been sexually harassed. that's second only to the military at 69 percent.
in part 2 of our issue on #metoo in stem, editor @dabeccaburton looks at the need for sexual harassers in academic fields to be held accountable.
this story comes out only months after @thenasem released their own report on sexual harassment in stem fields. read more at the link in our bio.

text:
ester y yo siempre practicamos "zse chuan" o serpiente con el que exponemos nuestra tensión y conexión. este método enseña a fluir manteniendo un nivel de relajación elevado y donde al mismo tiempo emitimos fuerza intermitente. este método a la vez es un ejercicio de iniciación a muchas técnicas de desequilibrio y luxación de chin na. así pues, podemos tenerlo como un método de #relajación, de práctica de fluidez  y de #meditación en movimiento a la vez que aprendemos los principios del combate 💪🙌👌 . .

ester and i always practice "zse chuan" or the exercise of the snake. with this exercise we expose our tension and #connection. this method teaches us to flow maintaining a high level of #relaxation and, at the same time, emitting intermittent #force. this method is also an initiation exercise to many chin na dislocation techniques. so, when we practice this exercise we  can use it as a method of #relaxation, #flow and #meditation in movement while we learn the principles of #combat .

#yinyang #chinna #mmaa #aamm #taichi #tuishou #combate #selfdefense #metoo #yoga #yogalife #lima #peru #train #artesmarciales #master #zsechuan

text:
this week had been so rough for many many wonderful women i know, including myself. of course i have a story and no, i don’t want to share it. the point however, and the thing that has made me ache in every part of my body, is knowing that so many wonderful humans hold these awful fucking memories
.
.
i’ve been teaching a lot lately and because of my crazy busy schedule, i lost focus on my own practice and thus have felt short sited and choppy in my teachings. maybe it’s because i’m busy but maybe it’s been because i feel lost and disheartened in our current society. i’m sure you have felt this too
.
.
this weekend, i didn’t check social media, i tuned out from the news, happily looked after visiting friends & spent every available second loving on my pups and beloved husband. finally, this morning i practiced. now i’m eating the largest muffin and drinking all the coffee before starting this week. we can do this, we must do this. keep fighting. keep loving. keep resisting. none of this was ever ok but we will be ♥️ #yoga #yogafeet #yogaeverydamnday #yogapractice #yogainspiration #iloveyoga #healing #yogameditation #morningyoga #morningyogapractice #stopkavanaugh #metoo #womenrights #strongwomen #fuckthepatriarchy #ibelivedrchristineblaseyford #christineblaseyford

text:
done!! i am finished with my 21 day reset! what did i learn……
.
i learned that if i slow down everybody in the house slows down. .
i learned that when i start feeling my stress and anxiety creep in, i can go outside, walk welly, and feel a lot better 20 min later.
.
i learned that i need more sleep, i am calmer, happier, and manage life better if i sleep 8 hours every night. .
i learned i can lose weight without working out for hours and hours. .
i learned to just be happier!!! .
these are the reasons i did this program, they are the most important take aways.  tomorrow i will focus on the physical changes! .
#swimmom #wisconsingirl  #ironmom #australianlabradoodle #happinessjourney #realmomlife #metoo #notalone #iseeyou #community #strongertogether #ibelieveher #ibelieveyou #believewomen #growthmindset #ilovemyhusband #rewardinglife
